#Implement Services and Business Logic
Create services ('DoctorService' and 'PatientService') to handle CRUD operations and business logic such as suggesting doctors based on patient symptoms.

#Implement Controller APIs
Define REST endpoints using Spring MVC annotations ('@RestController', '@GetMapping', '@PostMapping', etc.) to expose CRUD operations and the doctor suggestion logic.

#Implement Doctor Suggestion API
@RestController
@RequestMapping("/api")
public class DoctorController {
    
    @Autowired
    private DoctorService doctorService;

    @GetMapping("/suggest-doctors")
    public ResponseEntity<?> suggestDoctorsForPatient(@RequestParam Long patientId) {
        try {
            Patient patient = patientService.findById(patientId);
            if (patient == null) {
                return ResponseEntity.notFound().build();
            }

            List<Doctor> doctors = doctorService.findDoctorsByPatientSymptom(patient);
            if (doctors.isEmpty()) {
                return ResponseEntity.ok("There isnâ€™t any doctor present at your location for your symptom");
            }

            return ResponseEntity.ok(doctors);
        } catch (Exception e) {
            return ResponseEntity.status(HttpStatus.INTERNAL_SERVER_ERROR).build();
        }
    }
}
